<text>Barton Township is a civil township of Newaygo County in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2020 census, the township population was 706.

==Geography==
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of , of which is land and (0.11%) is water.

==Demographics==
As of the census of 2000, there were 820 people, 301 households, and 223 families residing in the township. The population density was . There were 382 housing units at an average density of . The racial makeup of the township was 98.29% White, 0.12% African American, 0.85% Native American, 0.12% Asian, 0.12% from other races, and 0.49% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 0.98% of the population.

