<text>Wilcox Township is a civil township of Newaygo County in the U.S. state of Michigan. The population was 1,133 at the 2020 census.

==Geography==
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of , of which is land and (0.26%) is water.

==Demographics==
