<doc id="118366" wikidata="Q7612841" url="?curid=118366" title="Steve Hindalong">
<text>Steve Hindalong (born November 29, 1959) is an American drummer, percussionist, songwriter and producer best known for his work with the alternative rock band the Choir. Since 2006, Hindalong has also been an official member of the alternative country supergroup Lost Dogs.

After becoming a prolific producer in the late 1990s, Hindalong received several Dove awards (2001 and 2003, &quot;Special Event Album of the Year&quot;) for his work on the &quot;City on a Hill&quot; project. Hindalong also co-wrote God of Wonders with Marc Byrd, which was used by NASA to wake up Discovery astronaut Michael Fossum.

==Discography==
===The Choir===
* &quot;Shades of Gray&quot; (1986) – Producer, Songwriter, Drums, Percussion
